article.headline: Radford 92, High Point 87 (2OT)
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Andre Bynum and Brandon Jeffers scored 21 points each to help Radford get by High Point 92-87 in double overtime Wednesday night. Both players also had solid all-around games for Radford (11-15, 5-10 Big South Conference), with Bynum dishing out seven assists and recording three steals and Jeffers handing out five assists and pulling down eight rebounds. Jerry Echenique had 23 points and eight rebounds for the Panthers (12-16, 7-8), while Akeem Scott added 20 and Arizona Reid had 10 points and 13 rebounds. The teams were tied at 68 at the end of regulation and at 81 after the first overtime. Radford was 7 for 12 in the extra periods and made 4-of-5 shots from 3-point range, while High Point hit just 6-of-15 field-goal attempts and missed all six of its 3-point tries. The Panthers didn't score a field goal in the last 2:12 of the game.
